Locked architectural decisions
1. Single error contract

Every Parmana API endpoint returns the same error envelope:

{
  "error": {
    "code": "...",
    "message": "..."
  }
}

This applies consistently across all resources.

2. Stable error codes

Clients must make programmatic decisions using the code field.

The message is intended for humans and may be revised for clarity without changing the API contract.

3. Optional diagnostic information

The following fields are optional:

details
timestamp
traceId

They provide additional diagnostic context without changing the error semantics.

4. No internal implementation details

Responses must never expose:

stack traces,
SQL queries,
filesystem paths,
internal exceptions,
cryptographic secrets,
implementation-specific details.
5. Deterministic failures

Errors do not partially modify immutable resources.

If a request fails:

no Business Transaction is created,
no Execution Trust Record is created,
no partial trust artifacts are persisted.
Canonical Principle (Locked)

Errors are deterministic, machine-readable, and consistent across the entire Parmana API.

Every failure is represented using a single canonical error envelope with stable error codes, optional diagnostic metadata, and no leakage of internal implementation details, preserving the integrity and predictability of the Execution Trust platform.


{
  "$schema": "https://json-schema.org/draft/2020-12/schema",
  "$id": "https://schemas.parmana.ai/common/error.schema.json",
  "title": "Error Response",
  "description": "Canonical error response returned by the Parmana API.",
  "type": "object",
  "additionalProperties": false,
  "required": [
    "error"
  ],
  "properties": {
    "error": {
      "type": "object",
      "additionalProperties": false,
      "required": [
        "code",
        "message"
      ],
      "properties": {
        "code": {
          "type": "string",
          "description": "Stable machine-readable error code.",
          "enum": [
            "INVALID_REQUEST",
            "INVALID_METADATA",
            "INVALID_POLICY",
            "INVALID_SIGNALS",
            "INVALID_SCHEMA",
            "UNAUTHENTICATED",
            "INVALID_TOKEN",
            "TOKEN_EXPIRED",
            "FORBIDDEN",
            "INSUFFICIENT_PERMISSIONS",
            "BUSINESS_TRANSACTION_NOT_FOUND",
            "EXECUTION_NOT_FOUND",
            "RECEIPT_NOT_FOUND",
            "POLICY_NOT_FOUND",
            "VERIFICATION_NOT_FOUND",
            "DUPLICATE_TRANSACTION",
            "OVERRIDE_NOT_ALLOWED",
            "IMMUTABLE_RESOURCE",
            "VERIFICATION_FAILED",
            "INVALID_SIGNATURE",
            "TRUST_RECORD_CORRUPTED",
            "POLICY_MISMATCH",
            "INTERNAL_ERROR",
            "STORAGE_FAILURE",
            "UNEXPECTED_ERROR"
          ]
        },
        "message": {
          "type": "string",
          "description": "Human-readable error description."
        },
        "details": {
          "type": "object",
          "description": "Optional structured error details.",
          "additionalProperties": true
        },
        "timestamp": {
          "type": "string",
          "format": "date-time",
          "description": "UTC timestamp when the error occurred."
        },
        "traceId": {
          "type": "string",
          "description": "Unique identifier for correlating logs and diagnostics."
        }
      }
    }
  },
  "examples": [
    {
      "error": {
        "code": "POLICY_NOT_FOUND",
        "message": "The requested policy 'payment-approval' version '2.1.0' could not be found.",
        "details": {
          "policy": "payment-approval",
          "version": "2.1.0"
        },
        "timestamp": "2026-06-26T13:00:00Z",
        "traceId": "TRC-7f8c4d9e"
      }
    },
    {
      "error": {
        "code": "DUPLICATE_TRANSACTION",
        "message": "A Business Transaction with the same identifier already exists with different content.",
        "timestamp": "2026-06-26T13:05:00Z",
        "traceId": "TRC-1a2b3c4d"
      }
    }
  ]
}